keyValuePair.Value: Are those two defeats a reality check?
People were talking about you as possible contenders. But %1s swept your boys aside in both games. Do you have to stop and look again at your plans now?
%1s are a good team, that's for sure.

We thought we'd be able to match %1s and we did that as far as effort went. But, when it came to quality, they were far too good for us. We know we've been well beaten. Let's look to them as an example and try to improve.
They must be favourites in the Final.

I was confident we'd give them two competitive games. As it's turned out, they've been far too good for us. Twice. We'll recover, though. We'll work to improve. And we'll back better next time around.
We needed more energy.

We conceded bad goals to a very good team and that meant it was going to be difficult. What worries me, though, is that we didn't ever make an impact going forward. We always knew we had to score. Where was the energy and the drive that we needed to give ourselves a chance?
What can you learn from these defeats?
Over the two legs, %1s looked stronger in every department. Now you're out and you have the chance to reflect, what do you think these defeats can teach you about your team?
We mustn't lose our heads over this.

We'd set qualifying as one of our targets this season so, of course, we're disappointed. But we can't feel sorry for ourselves. We have to be honest with each other, keep working hard and come back better than this next time round.

We'd set qualifying as one of our targets this season so, of course, we're disappointed. But we can't feel sorry for ourselves. We have to be honest with each other, keep working hard and come back better than this next time round.
I already knew how good %1s were.

Of course we were excited about the chance to qualify. But I knew all along we'd find it difficult. Yes, we should have been better, but %1s are a very good and experienced team. No complaints. They deserved to go through.
You have to be at your best against the best.
You have to be at your best against the best.

I think we were up against a team as good as any in the competition, so going out is no disgrace. But I expect to see more fight from a team of %1s players. We're going to have to have some very honest conversations about that.

I think we were up against a team as good as any in the competition, so going out is no disgrace. But I expect to see more fight from a team of %1s players. We're going to have to have some very honest conversations about that.
You fell at the last. What went wrong?
The advantage against %1s made no real difference. Even with the prize of a final in your sights, you had no answers to them and were beaten again. Is there anything else your boys could have done?
Maybe we needed a different approach.

Before I criticise my players, I have to analyse my own decisions. Perhaps our team shape put too much pressure on the boys in the transitions. We got caught on the break every time. Perhaps we should have taken a more cautious approach.
We can always be better.

Was there anything we could have done differently? Probably. But I won't jump to conclusions yet. I'll study the game, think about where we got caught out, and then decide how to make sure we're better in future.

Was there anything we could have done differently? Probably. But I won't jump to conclusions yet. I'll study the game, think about where we got caught out, and then decide how to make sure we're better in future.
We lost our way completely.

Against such a good team, it was vital everybody stuck to our plan. But in both games, individual players went out there thinking they knew better. We lost our shape, got exposed defensively and then, of course, got punished by quality players.
Well beaten in both games, how do your boys move forward now?
You must have hoped you'd have enough quality around the team to see you qualify. Instead, you've been soundly beaten twice and you're out. Pretty tough for you to swallow?
We've been taught a lesson.

The team made mistakes. I made mistakes, too, perhaps. What's important now is to look at the things we did wrong, be honest with ourselves, and have the humility to recognise we have to improve. %1s have taught bus some harsh lessons.
I was surprised how strong %1s were.
I'm not sure we ever managed to cope with %1s's intensity. I knew they were good, but they came into both games with even more than I expected. They caught us cold twice. So we're out.
We'll get nowhere playing like that.

I'm shocked by just how easy we've been to play through in these two games. I expected us to be better-organised and more resilient than that. As it is, we can have no complaints about being knocked out. I think we've let everyone down.
Did you ever feel you could get back into this tie?
The defeat in the first leg made things difficult and you weren't able to do more than draw with %1s today. Now you're out, how do you reflect on your own team's performance?
We couldn't create enough.

We knew we had to score goals today but, to be honest, we didn't ever get our passing game going. The opposition sat in deep and were able to get the draw they wanted. It's a blow not to qualify, that's for sure.
We're out so we have to move on.
We'll look back at this tie and we'll know it was lost in the first leg. But that's in the past now. Let's recover, work hard in training and move on. We've still got a lot of football to play.
That's a big chance we've let slip.

It was so important to the club to qualify and maybe the weight of expectation told on our players. It's not hard to understand why we've gone out. We played so poorly in the first leg. There was never much chance of us turning it round here.
Did you feel you ever had a chance of reaching the Final?
It's been a great run but your team's perhaps been found out over these past two games. You'd needed a big win to get back on terms today. Did you ever see it happening?
We needed early goals and nothing fell for us.

I'm proud the team made it this far in the competition. But, of course, that makes it even tougher to take going out. We were solid enough and tried to take the game to the opposition. But we needed an early goal and it just wouldn't come.
I expected us to put up more of a fight.

There was a place in the Final at stake! I know we had a lot to do but I really expected an %1s team to put up more of a fight. We moved the ball so slowly. Didn't ask enough questions. We made it easy for the opposition to hang on for the draw.
I'm upset, but this isn't about me.

It doesn't really matter how I'm feeling. The supporters had their hearts set on a place in the Final. We've let them down in both legs here. I can only apologise and promise we'll be working as hard as we can to improve.
You never had enough, did you?
You never had enough, did you?
It was always going to take something special to overturn that deficit from the first leg, but today was a let-down, wasn't it? Had the fight already been knocked out of your team?
It was always going to take something special to overturn that deficit from the first leg, but today was a let-down, wasn't it? Had the fight already been knocked out of your team?
We had pride to play for.

There were some better performances today but we'd left ourselves too much to do. We needed to get an early goal if we were going to have any chance and it just never happened. Tough on the boys. We'll have to put it down to experience.
They're a decent team and deserved to win.

I'm not going to get too down-hearted. We've been knocked out by an experienced outfit. I understand everyone's disappointed. But we're a developing team. I promise you'll see us winning games like this before long.

I'm not going to get too down-hearted. We've been knocked out by an experienced outfit. I understand everyone's disappointed. But we're a developing team. I promise you'll see us winning games like this before long.
We needed to make things happen.

I expected more from us. %1s fans deserve better. We talked about making a fast start but it never happened. Our mentality wasn't right at all. I think too many of our players had already decided there was no way this game could be won.
Is it fair to say you lost the tie in the first leg?
You knew you needed a big win today but you never built up any momentum. The opposition looked pretty comfortable holding out for the draw. Could your boys have given anything more?
We couldn't impose ourselves.

We took a bit of a hiding in the first leg, so we knew we'd need an early goal here to have any chance at all. We just weren't able to impose ourselves on the game, though. It was far too easy for the opposition to hang on.
Our first leg display didn't help!
We made life difficult for ourselves in that first leg. We were up against an experienced %1s team here. They took the sting out of the game today and saw it out for the draw to go through.
You make your own luck.

To be fair to the boys, we didn't get much luck today. But we defended so poorly in the first leg, I don't think there was ever much chance we'd be able to turn it round, even here in %1s. We were playing a good team and never looked like doing enough.
Has a bit of pride been restored?
You said yourself you were a shambles in the first leg and today was just about playing for pride. Did your team's attitude satisfy you, even though the win here wasn't enough for you to qualify?
Look, the boys had a go.

In the end, we got closer to them than I thought we would. We worked ever so hard and even got our noses in front here. But we're left regretting things going so wrong in the first leg. It's a shame but we'll have to move on.
It's heart-breaking, really.

I'm not going to dwell on the details. We all know what happened in the first leg. If we'd been half as good then as we were today, we'd have qualified. We've given the tie away, to be honest, and that hurts.
I thought we could have turned it round.

I know we were up against it. You'd have the ask the lads why they played so poorly in that first leg. I honestly thought, though, that we were still in with a chance. We won and that's restored some pride. But we didn't ever have quite enough. We didn't deserve to go through.

I know we were up against it. You'd have the ask the lads why they played so poorly in that first leg. I honestly thought, though, that we were still in with a chance. We won and that's restored some pride. But we didn't ever have quite enough. We didn't deserve to go through.
You threatened the comeback. Why didn't it happen?
You threatened the comeback. Why didn't it happen?
Winning this second leg restores some pride for the team, but you'll know better than anyone that you've missed out on the Final. How do you think the team can move forward from here?
Winning this second leg restores some pride for the team, but you'll know better than anyone that you've missed out on the Final. How do you think the team can move forward from here?
We've let the fans down.

The fans were incredible. Despite that terrible result in the first leg, they were right behind us the whole game here. We won, of course, but we just couldn't find enough to give those supporters the comeback they really deserved. We owe it to them to improve.
We'll learn from this experience.

Not many of our players have played at this level before. I think everybody connected with %1s can be proud we got this far in the competition. Still, it's heart-breaking. In the end, we just couldn't recover from that disaster in the first leg.

Not many of our players have played at this level before. I think everybody connected with %1s can be proud we got this far in the competition. Still, it's heart-breaking. In the end, we just couldn't recover from that disaster in the first leg.
We could have taken more risks.

After the first leg, the Final seemed a pretty remote possibility. Then we got in front here and I really thought the comeback was on. But, to be honest, we ran out of ideas, didn't we? It was easy enough for the opposition to hang on.

After the first leg, the Final seemed a pretty remote possibility. Then we got in front here and I really thought the comeback was on. But, to be honest, we ran out of ideas, didn't we? It was easy enough for the opposition to hang on.
Proud to have won here? Or full of regrets?

Your boys restored a bit of pride against %1s. But today's win wasn't enough to overturn their advantage from the first leg. You must be pleased with the performance, but how big a blow is it to go out?
We've come up short, I suppose.

I think the lads felt they had a point to prove after we suffered such a painful time of it in the first leg. I couldn't fault their attitude or their effort here. We came up short in the end, but at least we've shown we're a decent team after all.
We're out and we have to live with that.

Of course we were better this time and I'm happy with that. But the fact is we're out of the competition and that's a blow to everyone at the club. I hope we've learned some lessons from this experience.
We didn't do enough in the end.

Although we've won this game, I didn't think we ever looked like being able to overturn the result from the first leg. I'd hoped for more from us today with progress in the %1s on the line. We needed a special performance and the inspiration just wasn't there.
Would it be fair to say you had left yourselves too much to do?
You're out of the competition despite winning today. Would it be fair to say that the hammering you took in the first leg was always going to make it impossible for your boys to go through?
We should believe in ourselves.

Our supporters were incredible. Even though we let them down so badly in the first leg, they stuck behind us. I'm just sorry we couldn't find the goals we needed to pull off a comeback, but I hope they can still feel proud of the team. I just wish we could have had more belief in ourselves.
I have to take some of the responsibility here.

Before the game, I was worried about us getting hit on the break if we committed too many men forward. In hindsight, though, with our place in the %1s at stake, maybe I should have gone with a more adventurous line-up from the start. Who knows what might have happened then?
The damage had already been done.

I think the lads know that their performance in the first leg is the reason we're out. We were left with too much to do today. All I can say is that this win restores a bit of pride for us and we'll move on from here. But I've been very disappointed with us over the two legs, that's for sure.
A fantastic comeback. What inspired your team?
You took such a bad beating in the first leg, nobody gave you a chance of qualifying. But your players thought differently! What inspired the comeback?
We owed that result to our fans.
We let people down with our display in the first leg. But the fans stuck behind us and, once we got in front, the atmosphere here was incredible. That's what made the comeback possible.
We all know how important qualifying was for the club.

I think we felt the pressure in the first leg and suffered because of it. This game felt different, almost as if we had nothing to lose. The boys showed great courage and had the quality to pull off an amazing result.
I think we've sent out a message.

This could be a very important result for the club. We needed to qualify. The players have proved here that, if our attitude is right and we go out and play our football, then anything's possible for this team.
Did your own team surprise you with this performance?
That's as good a %1s comeback as anyone can remember, in any competition. You must be very proud of your players. Did they surprise even you with their performance?
We just never gave up.

Even after the first leg, I know the senior players were still convinced we could go through. The boys have proved a point. The key to the comeback was the winning mentality we're starting to see from this group. Let's push ourselves on from here now.
We're trying to build something here.

I'm very pleased for the boys. We're trying to build something at the club and results like this can only give them extra belief in what we're doing. It's another step on the journey, that's for sure.
Great attitude. Great result!

I expect certain qualities from a %1s team: fighting spirit, hard work, determination. Those are the things I saw out there today. Once we got in front here, I knew our creative players would inspire us to pull off something special. Great attitude from the boys. We deserved to go through.
%1s are into the Final. Is this a proud day for you?
%1s are into the Final. Is this a proud day for you?
It looked like %1s's chance had gone after that humiliation in the first leg. But your team proved what they're capable of today. Can they go on and lift the trophy now?
It looked like %1s's chance had gone after that humiliation in the first leg. But your team proved what they're capable of today. Can they go on and lift the trophy now?
Our players don't know how good they are!

I hope this comeback will give the players real belief in themselves. We looked unstoppable at times. We've always got goals in us so, if the lads can take that energy and ruthlessness into the %1s Final now, anything's possible for this team.
We have to develop a winning mentality.

I think the lads have proved something to the fans here. And maybe to themselves, too. We're definitely good enough to be in the Final. With the right attitude, maybe we're good enough to win it as well.
I'm proud of the lads after that.

After that terrible first leg, the players took plenty of criticism and rightly so. But it just made them more determined to put things right here. That attitude is what made this amazing comeback possible. A real %1s performance. On to the Final now!
Where did the boys find that performance?
Everyone had assumed you'd be out after the heavy defeat in the first leg. But the team was unrecognisable here: powerful, direct, full of desire. How did you mastermind that comeback?
It's all about the players.

I can try to help my players and send them out with a plan. But you need leaders on the pitch to make results like that possible. The lads were sensational. They ran the game here and the comeback always looked possible. I'm proud of them all.
An exciting performance, something to build on.
It's a great comeback and I'm very proud of the team. But, when all's said and done, it just means we're through to the next round. We've got plenty of work still to do if we want to go any further.
We've set a marker for ourselves.

That's what our supporters expect from a %1s team. We let them down in the first leg but I'm happy we turned it around. That's how solid we need to be in every game if we're going to go on and achieve things this season.
